Access Kibana: Open your web browser and navigate to the Kibana URL.
Login: Log in to Kibana using your credentials.
Go to Security: Once logged in, navigate to the Security section. This is usually found in the left-hand sidebar.
Role Mapping: Look for an option related to role mappings. This might be within the Security section or under a specific user management area.
Create Role Mapping: Find the option to create a new role mapping.
Define Mapping: Define the mapping by specifying the rules that determine which roles are assigned to users or groups. This typically involves specifying conditions based on attributes like usernames, groups, or roles.
Save: Once you've configured the role mapping, save your changes.
